Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum posted 28 points and nine assists for the visiting Boston Celtics, who breezed to a 123-93 win against the Atlanta Hawks.
Derrick White added 21 points while Payton Pritchard scored 18 points off the bench.
Jrue Holiday scored 16 points and Neemias Queta tallied 10 points and seven rebounds.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Hawks' Trae Young injured his rib and scored a career-low 2 points.
